{"key":"processedPost-6515580","value":{"id":6515580,"first":6515105,"last":6516185,"when":1170259590,"utime":"01/31/07 06:06 PM","content":"Don't use the oven.  Air is a poor conductor of heat, so the the material on the edges of your bag will be overcooked while the middle is still cool.  It's best to pasteurize straw in a bath so the hot water is around each and every piece, not trying to heat from the edges toward the middle.  Remember, straw is an insulator.<br />RR","title":"Re: Will the size of oven-bag matter for oven-pasteurization?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}